Wipe the konbu with a damp cloth. Cut it into 4-inch (10-cm) pieces and place in a medium saucepan with the water. Cover and bring to a boil. Lower the heat to mediumlow and simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour, or until the liquid has reduced to about 4 1/3 cups (1.1 l). Strain through a fine-mesh sieve and discard solids. Use immediately, or refrigerate for up to 3 days or freeze.